	'`. Header comment block (15-25 lines) cites WO-0086, P3-W10-F14, master-plan §4.4 line 328, DEC-0009, and the 4 sub-checks (cargo test, depcruise version, manifest existence, circular-dep smoke against tmpdir-fabricated module pair). (b) `REPO_ROOT="$(git rev-parse --show-toplevel)"; cd "$REPO_ROOT"`. (c) Single-gate skip: `if [[ "${UCIL_SKIP_ARCHITECTURE_PLUGIN_E2E:-0}" != "0" ]]; then echo '[SKIP] P3-W10-F14: architecture plugin smoke skipped via UCIL_SKIP_ARCHITECTURE_PLUGIN_E2E'; exit 0; fi` (extends the existing UCIL_SKIP_ARCHITECTURE_PLUGIN_E2E env-var from WO-0072 verbatim — single env-var per group; new tests reuse the existing gate per WO-0080 scope_out #14). (d) Assert depcruise on PATH: `if ! command -v depcruise >/dev/null 2>&1; then echo "[FAIL] P3-W10-F14: depcruise not on PATH; see scripts/devtools/install-dependency-cruiser.sh" >&2; exit 1; fi`. Print `depcruise --version` (first line) for the verifier log. (e) Assert manifest exists: `test -f plugins/architecture/dependency-cruiser/plugin.toml`. (f) Run cargo test: `cargo test -p ucil-daemon --test g4_plugin_manifests g4_plugin_manifests::dependency_cruiser_manifest_parses 2>&1 | tee "$CARGO_LOG" >/dev/null` then assert `grep -Eq 'test result: ok\. 1 passed; 0 failed|1 tests? passed' "$CARGO_LOG"`. (g) Circular-dep smoke (tmpdir-fabrication only — `tests/fixtures/typescript-project/**` is read-only per forbidden_paths, AND verified at planner-time the fixture is a clean DAG with NO existing cycle): `TMPDIR=$(mktemp -d)`, `trap 'rm -rf "$TMPDIR"' EXIT`, `cp -r tests/fixtures/typescript-project "$TMPDIR/ts-fixture"`, then ADD two files in the tmpdir copy creating a cycle (e.g., `cat > "$TMPDIR/ts-fixture/src/cycle-a.ts" <<'EOF'
import { fromB } from "./cycle-b.js";
export const fromA = () => fromB();
EOF` and `cat > "$TMPDIR/ts-fixture/src/cycle-b.ts" <<'EOF'
import { fromA } from "./cycle-a.js";
export const fromB = () => fromA();
EOF`). Run depcruise with the JSON output format and the no-circular rule: `cd "$TMPDIR/ts-fixture" && depcruise --output-type json --include-only '^src/' --no-config src 2>&1 | tee /tmp/wo-0086-depcruise.json` (NB: `--no-config` ensures we exercise dep-cruiser's default rule set without depending on a project-local `.dependency-cruiser.js` config; if dep-cruiser's defaults do NOT surface circular as a warning, the executor can opt to write a minimal `.dependency-cruiser.js` config file IN THE TMPDIR ONLY — never in tests/fixtures/**) — `--include-only '^src/'` constrains the scan to the source tree. (h) Assert circular-dependency surfaced in the JSON output: `jq -e '.summary.violations[] | select(.rule.name == "no-circular" or (.rule.severity == "warn" and (.from | contains("cycle-"))))' /tmp/wo-0086-depcruise.json` (must succeed, indicating dep-cruiser found at least one circular violation; the `cycle-a → cycle-b → cycle-a` cycle in the tmpdir-fabricated files satisfies this). If the executor finds dep-cruiser's default rule set does NOT report circulars (depcruise default rules vary by version), the executor MAY fabricate a minimal `.dependency-cruiser.js` config file IN THE TMPDIR with `forbidden: [{name: 'no-circular', severity: 'warn', from: {}, to: {circular: true}}]` (this MUST be in the tmpdir copy, NEVER in tests/fixtures/**, NEVER in the repo root). (i) On all-green print `[OK] P3-W10-F14` exit 0; on any failure print `[FAIL] P3-W10-F14: <reason>` exit 1. `chmod +x`.
